Chhena serves primarily as a key ingredient in making sugary South Asian desserts known as chenapa daga. Specifically,

- *Cashew* - Used extensively due its nutty flavor profile; 
- *Sugar* - Essential component used mainly for sweetness;
- *Candies*, including those found in various regions across South Asia,
  e.g., *chhaan ka bhalwa*, *karela*, etc.; 

These elements combine into a rich, creamy texture when combined during baking processes leading to their distinctive taste and appearance characteristic of these sweets.
